description:
You are a Verilog expert. Be concise and focused on the key points and avoid repetitive thoughts. Provide the Verilog code design directly.

Synchronous HDLC framing involves decoding a continuous bit stream of data to look for bit patterns that indicate the beginning and end of frames (packets). Seeing exactly 6 consecutive 1s (i.e., 01111110) is a "flag" that indicate frame boundaries. To avoid the data stream from accidentally containing "flags", the sender inserts a zero after every 5 consecutive 1s which the receiver must detect and discard. We also need to signal an error if there are 7 or more consecutive 1s. Create a Moore-type finite state machine to recognize these three sequences:

// (1) 0111110: Signal a bit needs to be discarded (disc).
// (2) 01111110: Flag the beginning/end of a frame (flag).
// (3) 01111111...: Error (7 or more 1s) (err).

// When the FSM is reset, it should be in a state that behaves as though the previous input were 0. The reset signal is active high synchronous. The output signals should be asserted for a complete cycle beginning on the clock cycle after the condition occurs.
Keep your reasoning process short and concise. Please complete the Verilog code below and return the complete module code:
```verilog

completion:
module top_module (
    input clk,
    input reset,
    input in,
    output reg disc,
    output reg flag,
    output reg err
);

  reg [3:0] state;

  localparam S_IDLE  = 4'b0000;
  localparam S_1     = 4'b0001;
  localparam S_11    = 4'b0010;
  localparam S_111   = 4'b0011;
  localparam S_1111  = 4'b0100;
  localparam S_11111 = 4'b0101;
  localparam S_111110 = 4'b0110;
  localparam S_111111 = 4'b0111;
  localparam S_ERR   = 4'b1000;

  always @(posedge clk) begin
    if (reset) begin
      state <= S_IDLE;
      disc <= 0;
      flag <= 0;
      err <= 0;
    end else begin
      disc <= 0;
      flag <= 0;
      err <= 0;

      case (state)
        S_IDLE: begin
          if (in) state <= S_1; else state <= S_IDLE;
        end
        S_1: begin
          if (in) state <= S_11; else state <= S_IDLE;
        end
        S_11: begin
          if (in) state <= S_111; else state <= S_IDLE;
        end
        S_111: begin
          if (in) state <= S_1111; else state <= S_IDLE;
        end
        S_1111: begin
          if (in) state <= S_11111; else state <= S_IDLE;
        end
        S_11111: begin
          if (in) state <= S_111111; else state <= S_IDLE;
        end
        S_111110: begin
          if (in) state <= S_1; else state <= S_IDLE;
          disc <= 1;
        end
        S_111111: begin
          if (in) state <= S_ERR; else begin state <= S_IDLE; flag <= 1; end
        end
        S_ERR: begin
          err <= 1;
          if (in) state <= S_ERR; else state <= S_IDLE;
        end
